post_text: Ready or not (and we are ready), we are starting school tomorrow for 1st - 12th grades. Yesterday's Open House had nearly 100% attendance at the elementary school. Our water filling stations have not arrived in the elementary building. If possible, please make sure your child's water bottle is full when they arrive for the remainder of the week. We will have bottled water available, also. Just a reminder, our bus loading zone has moved to the front of the building and parent drop-off /pickup is on the playground street going east to west. Students are not allowed in the building until 8 AM. School starts at 8:25 AM. Everyone is so excited for this memorable day!!

Good morning! South O’Brien Athletic Boosters will be having their monthly meeting this Tuesday July 13th at 6:30 pm in the commons at the high school.

Please consider joining this group as we are looking for new members. This is a great group that raises funds for our youth athletes! Without volunteers/members our kids would not have extra perks like speed/agility camps, update weight room equipment, uniforms, etc.

Our member numbers are low and we need to get them up or we will not have a booster club which will affect our athletes. Please come and check it out!

Please respond to this survey by midnight Wednesday.

HOUSEHOLD TECHNOLOGY ACCESS SURVEY

Please respond to the Household Technology Access Survey at the link below.

The survey should take no longer than five minutes to complete and will help the state and South O’Brien to better understand the specific technology needs of PK-12 and postsecondary learners. The information will help determine how to best use the Governor’s Emergency Education Relief (GEER), which focuses on providing and expanding broadband access and improving access to technology in other ways.

The survey will close at 11:59 PM (midnight) on Wednesday, June 24.

We strongly encourage one person in each household in the South O’Brien School District to complete the survey. Thank you for participating!

Survey link: http://bit.ly/iowatechsurvey

post_text: At last night's School Board meeting, Pizza Ranch provided a nice dinner to recognize Mr. Moore's 11 years as South O'Brien's Superintendent and 36 years in education. Mr. Moore is retiring at the end of the month. You have always preached hard-work and problem-solving to our students and staff. Your motto was "any problem can be solved with the right people in the room." South O'Brien sincerely thanks you for a job well done helping our students, staff, parents and community. District Motto- "Coming together as ONE, we are South O'Brien"!

post_text:
JH Students and Parents:

As many of you have already heard, Gov. Reynolds gave the ok for HS baseball and softball to resume practices beginning June 1. Unfortunately, JH programs are not allowed to commence at this time.

We have decided that we will be allowing 8th grade students the opportunity to play high school baseball and softball this summer. We have freshman schedules that will be filled with a combination of incoming and outgoing freshman.

If you are an 8th grader and you desire to play this summer, please reach out to your sport's head coach if you have not already done so (Baseball-Tanner Petersen, tpetersen@soswolverines.org; Softball-Heather Struve, hstruve@soswolverines.org) and let them know your interest so they can make appropriate accommodations. Please let these coaches know by the end of the day Thursday, May 28.

Practices will begin on June 1.

If you have other questions, please let me know and I'll do my best to get them answered.

Thanks,

Kent De Zeeuw, AD
South O'Brien Schools

post_text:
South O'Brien had about 15 freshmen submit projects to the State Science and Engineering Fair of Iowa, which this year, was virtual online.
Sophia Leng, Samantha Wilbur, and Leo Sells made the Top 24 Finals of the State. Although they did not earn any big scholarships or prizes at the virtual awards ceremony this morning, they competed well. Sophia was 1st place in the Microbiology category, earning $100, a T-shirt, pin, and certificate. Leo and Samantha were 2nd place in their categories of Biochemistry and Energy, and both receive T-shirts, certificates, and pins. Congrats again to these three 9th graders and their instructor, Kevin Brasser!

post_text:
STATE SCIENCE FAIR RESULTS
Sofie Leng earned 1st Place in the Microbiology Division, Leo Sells earned 2nd Place in the Biochemistry Division, and Samantha Wilbur earned 2nd Place in the Energy and Transportation Division at the State Science and Engineering Virtual Fair 2020. These three are the top #1 or #2 students in the State of Iowa, comprised of over 700 projects, in their divisions.
These three will now get "re-judged" LIVE by the state judging panel on ZOOM early next week.
South O'Brien has never before had three division champions or runners-up in the same fair, ever. The Finals judging on Zoom will determine cash and scholarship winners. These 3 students out of the 28 finalists will be competing for part of over $50,000 in cash prizes and scholarships.
Congratulations and Good Luck to Sofie, Leo, and Sam!

Sutherland Church of Christ
March 16 at 3:13 PM ·

With the closing of schools across Iowa, many kids and families are struggling with finances and specifically meals.
We are coming together as the Church in our communities along with help from area businesses to provide sack lunches to those in need. These are designed to be picked up, we are not encouraging the congregating of people. Although we were thinking first of children, these are available to anyone in need.
Locations for Sack Lunch Pick Ups are
Calumet- Fire Station- 113 W. 2nd Street
Paullina- Presbyterian Church- 103 W. Groesbeck
Primghar- Church of Christ- 280 1st SW (please use back door)
Sutherland- Church of Christ- 203 S. Oak St.
Sack Lunches are available 11:30-12:30 Weekdays March 17-April 10
If you are unable to pick up a lunch, i.e. you are high risk, staying home and would like a sack lunch delivered to your front door please call 712-446-3667, and leave a message.

post_text:
NATIONAL HISTORY DAY
South O’Brien Juniors enrolled in American Studies participated in the District competition hosted by Northwestern College in Orange City. Their projects ranged from Depression to Rap history. South O’Brien had four projects qualify for state.
**Kaeley Einck, Angela Nyunt, and Hannah Dau - Group website on Autism in the workplace.
**Bryce Rasmussen - individual exhibit on the Wright Brothers.
**Kylie Swanson - Individual Exhibit on Prince.
**Kadyn Steffens - Individual website on Moses Fleetwood.
Winners from district contests compete at the state contest for the chance to participate in the National History Day Contest in College Park, Maryland. The 2020 National History Day State Contest will be held Monday, April 27, 2020 at the Iowa Events Center in Des Moines.
CONGRATULATIONS to all of the students who participated on a job well done!

Upper Des Moines Opportunity, Inc.
November 21, 2019 at 11:13 AM ·

UDMO Obrien County was in great need in the month of November for our food pantry. 65 FCA ( Fellowship of Christian Athletes) members of the South Obrien School District went door to door in the community. This group did an amazing job collecting close to 1300 pounds of food. That was 1476 items total to put on the shelves of our food pantry. How awesome is that? Kids wanting to help feed their community, AMAZING!!!! We here at UDMO are so very blessed by your hard work and your dedication. Thank you for loving your community.

post_text:
SENIOR PICTURES ARE DUE TO MRS. FAUST BY December 10, 2019!

Please have your photographer email your selected photo to Kris Faust, yearbook advisor, at kfaust@soswolverines.org. If your photographer is unable to email the photo, bring a wallet size to Mrs. Faust and the yearbook staff will scan it. Please share this information with your photographer.

When you select your picture for school use, please remember the following requirements:
*Wallet size
*Vertical shot
*Head and shoulders or upper body shots preferred
*No people, animals, or objects (i.e. cars, guns) with the student

The picture you submit will be used for the following:
*Yearbook senior portrait section
*Senior slide show at Graduation
*Area newspaper Graduation supplements
*Class composite displayed in the high school commons

If you would like someone from the yearbook staff to take your photo, contact the office and they will get something arranged
Parents/Guardians - thanks for your help with this!

Families with student(s) riding the bus, please note:

Bus drivers will be handing out emergency bus route schedules to bus riders beginning today, October 23. Emergency bus routes are used when it is not safe for buses to travel on gravel roads. Emergency bus routes are NOT yet being used. Please keep the information for when they may be needed later this school year.
When emergency bus routes are needed, South O'Brien will make an announcement via radio, TV, website, and Facebook.

Bus route information can also be viewed online. https://www.soswolverines.org/district/transportation-bus-route/
